Document: class_@gdscript  
Path: godot/classes/class_@gdscript.rst  
Summary: Overview of deprecated and utility methods in GDScript, including color conversion, assertions, and resource loading.  

Color8(r8: int, g8: int, b8: int, a8: int = 255) → Color  
Deprecated: Use Color.from_rgba8() instead. Returns a Color from 8-bit integer channels (r8, g8, b8, a8), each divided by 255.0. Useful for matching exact Image color values. Example: Color8(255, 0, 0) equals Color(1, 0, 0). Note: Due to lower precision, Color8() values may not equal those from the standard Color constructor. Use Color.is_equal_approx() for comparisons.  

assert(condition: bool, message: String = "") → void  
Asserts condition is true; if false, generates an error and pauses the project in the editor. Message provides additional context. Warning: Code inside assert() runs only in debug/editor builds. Example: assert(speed >= 0, "speed limit is 20"). Note: assert() is a keyword, not a function.  

char(code: int) → String  
Returns a single-character String from a Unicode code point. Inverse of ord(). Example: char(65) → "A", char(129302) → "🤖". See also String.chr() and String.unicode_at().  

convert(what: Variant, type: Variant.Type) → Variant  
Deprecated: Use type_convert() instead. Converts what to the specified type. Example: convert([4, 2.5, 1.2], TYPE_PACKED_BYTE_ARRAY) → [4, 2, 1].  

dict_to_inst(dictionary: Dictionary) → Object  
Deprecated: Use JSON.to_native() instead. Converts a dictionary (from inst_to_dict()) back to an Object instance.  

get_stack() → Array  
Returns an array of dictionaries representing the current call stack. Example output: [{function:bar, line:12, source:res://script.gd}, ...]. Note: Backtraces require editor/debug builds or ProjectSettings.debug/settings/gdscript/always_track_call_stacks enabled.  

inst_to_dict(instance: Object) → Dictionary  
Deprecated: Use JSON.from_native() instead. Converts an Object to a Dictionary. Note: Only supports objects with attached GDScript files. Non-recursive; nested objects are not duplicated.  

is_instance_of(value: Variant, type: Variant) → bool  
Returns true if value is an instance of type. Type can be Variant.Type constants, Object-derived classes, or Scripts. Example: is_instance_of(a, Node). Note: Raises runtime error if type is invalid.  

len(var: Variant) → int  
Returns the length of a Variant (e.g., String length, array size, Dictionary count). Example: len([1,2,3]) → 4.  

load(path: String) → Resource  
Loads a Resource from an absolute path. Example: load("res://main.tscn") → PackedScene. Note: Relative paths are prefixed with "res://". Use preload() for runtime caching.  

ord(char: String) → int  
Returns the Unicode code point of a single-character String. Inverse of char(). Example: ord("A") → 65.  

preload(path: String) → Resource  
Loads a Resource at parse-time, acting as a reference. Path must be a constant String. Example: preload("res://diamond.tscn").instantiate(). Note: preload() is a keyword.  

print_debug(...) → void  
Like print(), but includes stack frames when debugging. Example output: "Test print At: res://test.gd:15:_process()".  

print_stack() → void  
Prints a stack trace. Example output: "Frame 0 - res://test.gd:16 in function '_process'".  

range(n: int) → Array  
Returns an array with a range. Usage: range(4) → [0,1,2,3]; range(0,6,2) → [0,2,4]. Note: Returns empty array if no values meet constraints.  

type_exists(type: StringName) → bool  
Deprecated: Use ClassDB.class_exists() instead. Returns true if the specified class exists in ClassDB. Example: type_exists("Sprite2D") → true.